        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Weather Based Crop Insurance Scheme&amp;quot; launched by the Horticulture and Food Processing Department, Government of Madhya Pradesh aims to protect farmers from weather-related losses through insurance coverage for selected crops cultivated during Kharif and Rabi seasons.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n  - **Insurance Coverage for Crops:** Provides protection to crops against losses caused by adverse weather conditions such as high or low temperatures, excess or deficient rainfall, and wind speed.\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to provide crop insurance protection to farmers against weather-related risks under the Pradhan Mantri Fasal Bima Yojana. It ensures financial support to farmers affected by adverse weather conditions.",
